      • test

        Map test​(Map<String,​Object> configData,
         Map<String,​Object> filterData)
  throws ConnectorException,
         InvalidCredentialException,
         InvalidAttributeValueException,
         OperationTimeoutException,
         MissingKeyException
        Implement this method to display the "Save and Test" connection button on the Add/Update connection page and test the connectivity between EIC and your target application. This method is currently applicable only for a Windows (Microservices-based) connector.
        Parameters:
        configData - Stores metadata and contains information about configurations required for establishing the connection between the EIC and the target application.
        filterData - In Saviynt Security Manager(SSM/ECM),when creating a new ConnectionType(Example: ConnectionType name: sampleConnType) connection attributes are defined for different tasks such as reconciliation, provisioning(createaccount,addaccesstoaccount etc) in the form of JSON's(Example:ReconcileJSON,addAccesstToAccountJSON) for the selected sampleconnector.Upon having a connection Type for sampleconnector, a new connection is to be created.At the time of creating a new connection, ConnectionType(Example:sampleconntype) is chosen and connection attributes are dynamically populated. These connection attributes need to be inputed with relative data.For Example, ReconcileJSON need to be inputed with objects Users,Account,Entitlement (Example: 
        "ACCOUNT" : [ { "saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "ACCOUNT_ATTRIBUTES" : [ {"saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "USERS" : [ "saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty","sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "ENTITLEMENT" : [ {"saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ]
        data holds all these inputed details of JSON attributes from connection.
        Returns:
        The map
        Throws:
        ConnectorException - The connector exception
        InvalidCredentialException - The invalid credential exception
        InvalidAttributeValueException - The invalid attribute value exception
        OperationTimeoutException - The operation timeout exception
        MissingKeyException - The missing key exception

      • reconcile

        void reconcile​(Map<String,​Object> configData,
               Map<String,​Object> filterData,
               String formatterClass)
        throws ConnectorException
        Implement this method to import accounts and entitlements from the target application

        This method performs the tasks in the below sequence:

        • Retrieves the connection attributes from the data parameter.
        • Connects to the target application.
        • Performs account import based on the value specified in the IMPORTABLE_OBJECT attribute of the data parameter.
        • Collects the data required for accounts or entitlements import from the target application.
        • Converts the data in the format that the notify() method of Saviynt Connector Framework accepts for processing the reconciliation data.
        Parameters:
        configData - Stores metadata and contains information about configurations required for establishing the connection between the EIC and the target application.
        filterData - In Saviynt Security Manager(SSM/ECM),when creating a new ConnectionType(Example: ConnectionType name: sampleConnType) connection attributes are defined for different tasks such as reconciliation, provisioning(createaccount,addaccesstoaccount etc) in the form of JSON's(Example:ReconcileJSON,addAccesstToAccountJSON) for the selected sampleconnector.Upon having a connection Type for sampleconnector, a new connection is to be created.At the time of creating a new connection, ConnectionType(Example:sampleconntype) is chosen and connection attributes are dynamically populated. These connection attributes need to be inputed with relative data.For Example, ReconcileJSON need to be inputed with objects Users,Account,Entitlement (Example: 
        "ACCOUNT" : [ { "saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "ACCOUNT_ATTRIBUTES" : [ {"saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "USERS" : [ "saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty","sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ], "ENTITLEMENT" : [ {"saviyntproperty": "Inputsaviyntproperty", "sourceproperty": "${Inputsourceproperty}" } ]
        data holds all these inputed details of JSON attributes from connection.
        formatterClass - The formatter class
        Throws:
        ConnectorException - the connector exception

      • checkExisting

        Boolean checkExisting​(Map<String,​Object> configData,
                      Map<String,​Object> data,
                      SearchableObject serachableObject)
               throws ConnectorException
        To check existing record for the input object.

        Example : To check existing record for the input object(for account) , refer to the below steps:

        Step 1 : Retrieve connection attributes from configData/Data.

        Step 2 : Set the data with filters if any.

        Step 3 : Call getObjectList.

        Step 4 : Return true if object exists.

        Parameters:

        data - Stores both connection information and additional dynamic attributes that are added during runtime. This parameter accepts values in the JSON format or fields
        serachableObject - For serachableObject
        Returns:
        The boolean true or false
        Throws:
        ConnectorException - The connector exception

      • createAccount

        Map createAccount​(Map<String,​Object> configData,
                  Map<String,​Object> data)
           throws ConnectorException
        Implement this method to create an account.

        This method performs the tasks in the below sequence:

        • Retrieves the connection attributes from the data parameter to connect with the target application.
        • Creates an account based on the value specified in the ACCOUNTID attribute of the data parameter.
        • Replaces the binding variables in the connection attributes using the GroovyService.convertTemplateToString method from the com.saviynt.ssm.abstractConnector.utility package of Saviynt Connector Framework.
        • Returns data in the form of Map with metadata to process the provisioning data.
          • If you want to return or update the newly created account attributes from the target application into EIC, create a map containing your account attributes and send it to EIC in the Map (Java) format as below:map.put("provisioningData", <map containing your account attributes>)
          • If you do not want to return or update the newly created account attributes, send a null value as below.map.put("provisioningData", null)
        Parameters:
        configData - Stores metadata and contains information about configurations required for establishing the connection between the EIC and the target application.
        data - Stores both connection information and additional dynamic attributes that are added during runtime. This parameter accepts values in the JSON format or fields
        Returns:
        The map
        Throws:
        ConnectorException - The connector exception

      • setConfig

        void setConfig​(ConfigDataVo configData)
        Implement this method to configure the connection parameters. These parameters are displayed on the Add/Update Connection page of your connector.
        • Define all connection parameters by adding them in configData.getConnectionAttributes() list.
        • Define mandatory connection parameters by adding them in configData.getRequiredConnectionAttributes() list
        • Define encrypted connection parameters by adding them in configData.getEncryptedConnectionAttributes() list.
        • Add description for connection parameters using configData.setConnectionAttributesDescription(jsonObject.toString())
        Parameters:
        configData - Stores metadata and contains information about configurations required for establishing the connection between the EIC and the target application.
